HEADWORD: Dimplement
<hw>Dim"ple*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of
being dimpled, or marked with gentle depressions.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ground's most gentle <qex>dimplement</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dimply</ent>⟦br⟧
